There are two different types of patents, a Utility Patent and a Design Patent.  A utility patent is meant to protect the way an invention works, so something that has a unique function, process or method.  A Design Patent is meant to protect the way an invention looks, so something that has a unique outward appearance to a manufacture product.  The provisional application is only meant for inventions that would qualify for a Utility Patent. 

